@ccgod This distortion of distances and scales is not shown only by magnifying the view on the viewscreen. You can take for example battles between ships in the normal Star Trek. 

Helmsman says _"enemy ship is 1000 km from us"_ and then there is an externall camera shot showing both ships next to each other. If one ship is 641 m long, on TV screen it takes 10 cm, the other ship is 1042 m long and on screen takes 18 cm, then those 15  cm of distance between them on the TV screen clearly cannot be equal to 1 000 000 meter. 

However, I agree that in this very trailer, it looks particulary bad. Good TV maker is trying to balance the aspects of realism with the visual needs of TV production. Bad TV maker only cares on how cool it looks on screen.

